trans-unit.source: Generally, some CSS properties don't make sense on the toplevel window node, such as margins or padding. When client-side decorations without invisible borders are in use (i.e. the .solid-csd style class is added to the main window node), the CSS border of the toplevel window is used for resize drags. In the .csd case, the shadow area outside of the window can be used to resize it.
trans-unit.target: 一般来说,有些CSS属性在toplevel窗口节点上是没有意义的,比如margins或padding。当使用没有隐形边框的客户端装饰时(即在主窗口节点上添加了.solid-csd样式类),toplevel窗口的CSS边框被用于调整大小拖动。在.csd的情况下,可以使用窗口外的阴影区域来调整窗口的大小。

trans-unit.source: Generally, the drawing cycle begins when GTK receives a frame event from the underlying windowing system: if the user drags a window over another one, the windowing system will tell the underlying surface that it needs to repaint itself. The drawing cycle can also be initiated when a widget itself decides that it needs to update its display. For example, when the user types a character in an entry widget, the entry asks GTK to queue a redraw operation for itself.
trans-unit.target: 一般来说,当GTK收到来自底层窗口系统的帧事件时,绘图周期就开始了:如果用户在另一个窗口上拖动一个窗口,窗口系统会告诉底层表面需要重新绘制自己。绘制周期也可以在widget本身决定需要更新显示时启动。例如,当用户在一个入口widget中输入一个字符时,该入口会要求GTK为自己排队进行重绘操作。

trans-unit.source: Gestures are a set of specific controllers that are prepared to handle pointer and/or touch events, each gesture implementation attempts to recognize specific actions out the received events, notifying of the state/progress accordingly to let the widget react to those. On multi-touch gestures, every interacting touch sequence will be tracked independently.
trans-unit.target: 手势是一组准备处理指针和/或触摸事件的特定控制器,每个手势实现都试图从接收到的事件中识别出特定的动作,并相应地通知状态/进度,让小组件对这些动作做出反应。在多点触控手势上,每一个交互的触控序列都会被独立跟踪。

trans-unit.source: Gestures have a notion of “state” for each individual touch sequence. When events from a touch sequence are first received, the touch sequence will have “none” state, this means the touch sequence is being handled by the gesture to possibly trigger actions, but the event propagation will not be stopped.
trans-unit.target: 对于每个单独的触摸序列，手势都有“状态”的概念。当首次接收到来自触摸序列的事件时，该触摸序列将处于“无”状态，这意味着该手势正在处理该触摸序列以可能触发动作，但是不会停止事件传播。

trans-unit.source: Group name for tab drag and drop.

Grouped gestures always share the same state for a given touch sequence, so setting the state on one does transfer the state to the others. They also are mutually exclusive, within a widget where may be only one gesture group claiming a given sequence. If another gesture group claims later that same sequence, the first group will deny the sequence:
trans-unit.target: 对于给定的触摸序列,分组手势总是共享相同的状态,因此设置其中一个手势的状态会将其转移到其他手势上。它们也是相互排斥的,在一个小组件中,可能只有一个手势组要求一个给定序列。如果另一个手势组稍后要求使用相同的序列,则第一个手势组将否认该序列。

trans-unit.source: Grouping a “drag” gesture with a “pan” gesture will only effectively allow dragging in the panning orientation, as both gestures share state.
trans-unit.target: 由于两个手势共享状态，因此将“拖动”手势与“平移”手势分组只会有效地允许在平移方向上拖动。

trans-unit.source: Groups also perform an "implicit grabbing" of sequences, if a GdkEventSequence state is set to GTK_EVENT_SEQUENCE_CLAIMED on one group, every other gesture group attached to the same GtkWidget will switch the state for that sequence to GTK_EVENT_SEQUENCE_DENIED.
trans-unit.target: 如果在一个组上将GdkEventSequence状态设置为GTK_EVENT_SEQUENCE_CLAIMED，则组也会执行序列的“隐式捕获”，附加到同一GtkWidget的每个其他手势组都会将该序列的状态切换为GTK_EVENT_SEQUENCE_DENIED。

GtkButton — A widget that emits a signal when clicked on
trans-unit.target: GtkButton —单击时发出信号的小部件

trans-unit.source: GtkButton has a single CSS node with name button. The node will get the style classes .image-button or .text-button, if the content is just an image or label, respectively. It may also receive the .flat style class.
trans-unit.target: GtkButton有一个名为button的CSS节点。如果内容只是图片或标签,该节点将分别得到.image-button或.text-button样式类。它也可能得到.flat样式类。
